World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

          World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

          The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

          It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

          This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

          View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

          Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

          Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

          After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

              World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

              The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

              It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

              This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

              View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

              Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

              Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

              After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                      World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                      The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                      It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                      This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                      View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                      Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                      Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                      After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                          World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                          The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                          It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                          This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                          View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                          Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                          Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                          After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                              World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                              The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                              It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                              This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                              View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                              Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                              Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                              After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                                  World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                                  The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                                  It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                                  This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                                  View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                                  Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                                  Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                                  After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                                      World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                                      The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                                      It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                                      This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                                      View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                                      Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                                      Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                                      After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                                          World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                                          The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                                          It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                                          This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                                          View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                                          Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                                          Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                                          After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.

                                                  World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences

                                                  The life sciences subject ranking uses the same trusted and rigorous performance indicators as the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2024, but the methodology has been recalibrated to suit the individual fields.

                                                  It highlights the universities that are leading across the following disciplines: agriculture and forestry, biological sciences, veterinary science, and sport science.

                                                  This years table includes 1,059 universities, up from 1,017 last year.

                                                  View the World University Rankings 2024 by subject: life sciences methodology

                                                  Harvard University maintains its top ranking. The US holds 12 of the top 20 positions one fewer than last year. While the University of Pennsylvania joins this group at 17th, up from 21st, the universities of Washington and California, San Diego drop out.

                                                  Several top Asian universities have improved, including Chinas Peking University, which climbs to joint 12th from 18th; the National University of Singapore, which rises one place to 22nd; and the University of Tokyo, which jumps to 30th, after being 38th last year.

                                                  After the US and the UK, the most-represented nation in the top 100 is Germany, followed by Australia and China.
